nodes.bodyText:
It seems that for non-flattened correlated subquery, we are not collecting all the expressions. Here is an example:
create table t1 (a1 int, b1 int, c1 int, d1 int);
create index idx_t1 on t1 (a1+1, b1+2);
create table t2 (a2 int, b2 int, c2 int, d2 int);

explain select 1 from t1 --splice-properties index=idx_t1
where a1+1 not in (select a2 from t2 where b1+2 =b2);

In this case, I don't see the expression a1+1 being collected. This condition is in the PR node underneath SubqueryNode but above the SELECT node, so we may examine that also.

